---
export const prerender = false;

import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, FOUNDER_PLAYING_SINCE } from '../consts';

const yearsPlaying = new Date().getFullYear() - FOUNDER_PLAYING_SINCE;
const nonce = Astro.locals.nonce;

const organizationSchema = {
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@type": "Organization",
	"@id": "https://simic.systems/#organization",
	"name": "Simic Systems",
	"legalName": "Simic Systems LLC",
	"url": "https://simic.systems/",
	"logo": {
		"@type": "ImageObject",
		"url": "https://simic.systems/logo.png"
	},
	"email": "contact@simic.systems",
	"telephone": "+16055534735",
	"description": "Online retailer specializing in factory-sealed Magic: The Gathering products including booster boxes and collector sets. Ships across the US.",
	"areaServed": "US",
	"founder": {
		"@type": "Person",
		"name": "Jacob Banghart",
		"jobTitle": "Founder"
	}
};
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About Simic Systems | Online MTG Sealed Products Store" description="Simic Systems is run by a lifelong Magic: The Gathering player and collector in North Hollywood, CA. Factory-sealed MTG products shipped across the US via USPS Ground Advantage." />
		<script type="application/ld+json" nonce={nonce} set:html={JSON.stringify(organizationSchema)}></script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article>
				<h1>About Simic Systems</h1>
				<p><em>Last updated: July 13, 2026</em></p>

				<p>
					Simic Systems is an online store built by Jacob Banghart, who's been playing and collecting Magic: The Gathering since {FOUNDER_PLAYING_SINCE} (that's {yearsPlaying} years now) and is based in North Hollywood, California. What started as a deep love for the game turned into a mission: make it easier to buy sealed MTG product from someone who actually knows what they're selling.
				</p>

				<p>
					The trading card market can be rough to navigate: inflated prices, mystery condition items, sellers who've never shuffled a deck. Simic Systems runs on straightforward pricing, factory-sealed product only, and a seller who cares about the game as much as you do.
				</p>

				<h2>What We Carry</h2>
				<p>
					We stock factory-sealed Magic: The Gathering products with a focus on current and recent sets. Everything in the catalog is sealed in its original packaging, exactly as it left the manufacturer.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Play Booster Displays:</strong> the current standard booster format for drafting and opening</li>
					<li><strong>Collector Booster Displays:</strong> premium boxes loaded with foils, extended arts, and special treatments</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					The catalog is intentionally focused. We carry what we know, and we keep quantities accurate in real time, so there's no phantom stock and no orders that ship weeks late because something was already gone.
				</p>

				<h2>Shipping & Orders</h2>
				<p>
					All orders ship within the United States via <strong>USPS Ground Advantage</strong>. Orders are typically packed and handed off within 1–3 business days. You'll get a tracking number the moment your order ships. Orders over $250 require a signature on delivery, since sealed MTG product is valuable and we want it to reach you safely.
				</p>
				<p>
					We don't accept returns on sealed product. Once a box is in someone else's hands, its seal integrity can't be guaranteed. If something arrives damaged or we made a mistake on the order, reach out within 7 days and we'll make it right.
				</p>

				<h2>Get in Touch</h2>
				<p>
					Questions about an order, a product, or just want to talk MTG? Use the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or email <a href="mailto:contact@simic.systems">contact@simic.systems</a>. Response time is typically within one business day.
				</p>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
<style>
	main {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
	}
	article h1 {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	article h2 {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	ul, ol {
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}
	li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
</style>
